net.bytebuddy.dynamic

Interface DynamicType.Builder.FieldValueTarget<S>

  • Type Parameters:
    S - The most specific known type of the dynamic type, usually the type itself, an interface or the direct super class.
    All Superinterfaces:
    DynamicType.Builder<S>, DynamicType.Builder.FieldAnnotationTarget<S>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    DynamicType.Builder.AbstractBase.DefaultFieldValueTarget
    Enclosing interface:
    DynamicType.Builder<T>

    public static interface DynamicType.Builder.FieldValueTarget<S>
extends DynamicType.Builder.FieldAnnotationTarget<S>
    A builder to which a field was just added such that default values can be defined for the field. Default values must only be defined for static fields of a primitive type or of the String type.

      • value

        DynamicType.Builder.FieldAnnotationTarget<S> value(boolean value)
        Defines a boolean value to become the optional default value for the recently defined static field. Defining such a boolean default value is only legal for fields that are represented as an integer within the Java virtual machine. These types are the boolean type, the byte type, the short type, the char type and the int type.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to be defined as a default value for the recently defined field.
        Returns:
        A field annotation target for the currently defined field.

      • value

        DynamicType.Builder.FieldAnnotationTarget<S> value(int value)
        Defines an int value to be become the optional default value for the recently defined static field. Defining such an integer default value is only legal for fields that are represented as an integer within the Java virtual machine. These types are the boolean type, the byte type, the short type, the char type and the int type. By extension, integer types can also be defined for long types and are automatically converted.
        Parameters:
        value - The value to be defined as a default value for the recently defined field.
        Returns:
        A field annotation target for the currently defined field.
